a sizeable cash payment as part of the transaction, it remains unclear how that would be achieved. Walmart, which had previously partnered with Microsoft to make an outright bid for TikTok’s US business, remains interested in investing as well and could end up with a seat on the board of the new company, according to one of the people. The people asked not to be identified because the conversations were private. Separately, Democratic nominee Joe Biden assailed Trump for the timing of his interest in the app. Tech Central Vanguard President Trump said he won’t give Chinese tech giant ByteDance any more time to sell TikTok’s US operations before the feds ban the popular app. “We’ll either close up TikTok in this country for security reasons or it’ll be sold,” Trump told reporters Thursday before a trip to Michigan. “I’m… September 11, 2020 In "Technology" TikTok’s Beijing-based parent company is reportedly in talks with the US government about a possible deal to avoid an outright sale of the popular app’s US operations. ByteDance and top US officials are negotiating possible arrangements that would allow it to maintain some ownership stake in TikTok while still satisfying… September 10, 2020 In "News" Ahead of a deadline set by US President, Donald Trump, over video-sharing app, TikTok, the nation's officials will evaluate a bid that could see American tech giant Oracle become a partner to a Chinese company that has been called a national security risk. Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin confirmed on Monday… September 14, 2020 In "Technology"